The Beginning
1 In the beginning God created the heavens and the earth. 2 Now the earth was formless and empty, darkness was over the surface of the deep, and the Spirit of God was hovering over the waters.

3 And God said, “Let there be light,” and there was light. 4 God saw that the light was good, and he separated the light from the darkness. 5 God called the light “day,” and the darkness he called “night.” And there was evening, and there was morning—the first day.

6 And God said, “Let there be a vault between the waters to separate water from water.” 7 So God made the vault and separated the water under the vault from the water above it. And it was so. 8 God called the vault “sky.” And there was evening, and there was morning—the second day.

9 And God said, “Let the water under the sky be gathered to one place, and let dry ground appear.” And it was so. 10 God called the dry ground “land,” and the gathered waters he called “seas.” And God saw that it was good.

11 Then God said, “Let the land produce vegetation: seed-bearing plants and trees on the land that bear fruit with seed in it, according to their various kinds.” And it was so. 12 The land produced vegetation: plants bearing seed according to their kinds and trees bearing fruit with seed in it according to their kinds. And God saw that it was good. 13 And there was evening, and there was morning—the third day.

14 And God said, “Let there be lights in the vault of the sky to separate the day from the night, and let them serve as signs to mark sacred times, and days and years, 15 and let them be lights in the vault of the sky to give light on the earth.” And it was so. 16 God made two great lights—the greater light to govern the day and the lesser light to govern the night. He also made the stars. 17 God set them in the vault of the sky to give light on the earth, 18 to govern the day and the night, and to separate light from darkness. And God saw that it was good. 19 And there was evening, and there was morning—the fourth day.

20 And God said, “Let the water teem with living creatures, and let birds fly above the earth across the vault of the sky.” 21 So God created the great creatures of the sea and every living thing with which the water teems and that moves about in it, according to their kinds, and every winged bird according to its kind. And God saw that it was good. 22 God blessed them and said, “Be fruitful and increase in number and fill the water in the seas, and let the birds increase on the earth.” 23 And there was evening, and there was morning—the fifth day.

24 And God said, “Let the land produce living creatures according to their kinds: the livestock, the creatures that move along the ground, and the wild animals, each according to its kind.” And it was so. 25 God made the wild animals according to their kinds, the livestock according to their kinds, and all the creatures that move along the ground according to their kinds. And God saw that it was good.

26 Then God said, “Let us make mankind in our image, in our likeness, so that they may rule over the fish in the sea and the birds in the sky, over the livestock and all the wild animals,[a] and over all the creatures that move along the ground.”

27 So God created mankind in his own image,
    in the image of God he created them;
    male and female he created them.

28 God blessed them and said to them, “Be fruitful and increase in number; fill the earth and subdue it. Rule over the fish in the sea and the birds in the sky and over every living creature that moves on the ground.”

29 Then God said, “I give you every seed-bearing plant on the face of the whole earth and every tree that has fruit with seed in it. They will be yours for food. 30 And to all the beasts of the earth and all the birds in the sky and all the creatures that move along the ground—everything that has the breath of life in it—I give every green plant for food.” And it was so.

31 God saw all that he had made, and it was very good. And there was evening, and there was morning—the sixth day.

The basic setup for getting mana is having 4 Mana Spreaders which are crafting using living wood pointing into a Mana Pool which is made by using the living rock.

The main way to generate mana in the early game is by using endoflames since they are the most efficient. You can look up their recipe in JEI. To use them, place them around your mana spreaders which should  be about 1 block up and 2 blocks across from your mana pool. You can change your wand to function mode by shift-right clicking in the air and hovering over an endoflame with it in hand.

This will show you if it is connected for not, you will see a little icon with a mana spreader and a checkmark. 

Endoflames work by burning combustable materials such as coal in return for mana. Simply throw the item you'd like to convert on an endoflame and it will work once you hear the sound.

betterquesting:10.desc:8:
Welcome to this terrible mod that features both blood and magic combined. If you are unsure whether you are willing to sacrifice yourself and your friends that you may be playing with multiple times then I reccomend you ask someone else to do this questline for you as it is quite morbid. Or you could just sacrifice thousands of villagers.


This is the link to the FTB wiki with a guide for this mod as you may need it especially with building alters in later tiers. §n§r
https://ftb.fandom.com/wiki/Getting_Started_(Blood_Magic)


Anyways, to begin this mod you must first capture the demonic will of mobs. This is made convenentally easy with the snares. All you need to do is throw a snare at a mob, wait for the particles and then kill it to collect its demonic will. Fun!

Now I know what you're thinking... That's a complete lie I have no clue what you are thinking. For this quest just simply obtain a blood altar by using your newly aquired Demonic will. You will also need a sacrifical dagger to get some blood into the thing.
By putting a diamond into a blood altar and supplying it with sufficient blood, it will become a Weak Blood Orb. This is the first blood orb and as you guessed, the weakest.
Very simple item but very crucial for the rest of this mod.

The weakest and lowest capacity of all the gems. These gems act like demonic wills in that, when you kill a mob and take it's demonic will the will will automatically go into the gem until it is full of demonic will.

This weapon is very usefull in blood magic as killing an enemy with it will cause it's demonic will to drop. This sword acts as the snare as it is capable of taking a creature's demonic will.

This is also the first recipe that requires a source of demonic will to "power it". You may have noticed in the Hellfire forge there is a single slot to the very right, this is the "fuel" slot. 

Adding demonic will in the form of demonic will or tartaric gems will give the forge power and allow it function. 

My personal reccomendation is to have 2 tartaric gems. One for upgrading and the other for fueling.

I'd also reccomend that you build a mob farm so that you can easily farm demonic will.
By soaking a stone in your blood, you will get a blank slate. You can use hoppers to automate.

You may have been out of blood trying to make just one of these and I have some good news for you. The entire mod is built off of these miserable little blocks so you better find an efficient way to get them. They are also the key items needed to craft higher tier blood altars.

The Second more excruitating tier to make.

Building it is actually really simple, just surround the layer below your blood altar with the 8 blank runes.

For further instructions, consult the book that was given to you at the start or the wiki.

By placing this funny little thing directly underneath your blood alter, first off your dagger will look a bit funny but pricking yourself will remove all but half a heart and grant you more blood I think. That last part I'm not too sure on but why else would the thing exist it's not like I can't click several times to diminish my health.
The second tier of slate made from infusing a blank slate in a tier 2 blood altar.
This is the second tier blood orb made from infusing a block of redstone in the tier 2 blood altar.

This along with the Rune of Self Sacrifice are, in my opinion, the only 2 good runes to use. Basically instead of using a blank rune around your altar, you replace it with a special rune.

If you didn't know, the rune of capacity gives your blood altar more blood capacity.
So basically, this rune is busted. When you prick yourself, you get more blood. That's it no cap fr. Important not: You can mix and match different runes and they can be placed anywhere on the altar.

This blood altar is very easy to make it just requires a bit more blank runes, 8 stone bricks and 4 glowstone. You will build another layer of blank runes beneath and across one to the first layer of blank runes. You should be placing 5 blank runes on each side of the altar and connecting them will be stone bricks. When you place the stone bricks, do not place them in the corners ajacent to the different side's blank runes, instead place them one block above and then the other stone brick right on top of the first one. You should have 4 pillars that are 2 blocks high of stone bricks then place your glowstone ontop of each pillar and that's it. 

For further clarification, consult the book or the wiki.

This tier is considerably harder than the past three to construct as not only will you need a ridiculous amount of blank runes or runes of your choice, but you will also require bloodshards.

The layout of this altar is... complicated so much so that I'm not gonna try to explain it to you and instead just tell you to consult the wiki or the book.
This item is crucial for making the bound blade.
This is the second tier tartaric gem that you will make. At this point you should be making 2 of them, one for use and the other as fuel.

This tier gem allows for you to do the fun stuff.

Once again I'd reccomend that you make 2, but it's up to you. 

With this, you will have sufficient willpower for some of the crafts in this mod.
Use this by right clicking on placed arcane ashes. Do not fear, this is all part of the process.

This is the item required to obtain bloodshards which are nessesary for creating the Tier 4 Blood Altar.

At this point, you can also make Bound Armour which gives buffs for using it, but it is not nessesary.

To make, simply start the ritual and watch the animation since it is kinda cool.

By Shift Rightclicking with the bound blade in hand, you will activate it. 

Note that when it is activated, it will drain your health slowly, so beware of that.

Anyways, you that you have it, killing a mob will reward you with bloodshards sometimes. Fun.

The key item needed to build the tier 4 altar.

First, make bloodstone tiles then 2x2 craft them to make bloodstone bricks.

They also make cool decoration.

Must be glad to get here.

Anyways, this tier is actually kinda easy in MY opinion. The only challenge apart from the blank runes being the 4 beacons. 

I do not think that they have to be activated but I could be wrong.

Anyways, goodluck!
Note: You could just skip all the receeding tiers and just get this one since its like the only needed one.

Goodluck!

This item serves as the endgame item for Blood Magic. Don't lose it!



There is nothing new/different that you will have to do to obtain this item. The living armour is made the same way as the bound blade and everything else is very easy to make with the help of JEI. 

My reccomendation is to make some sort of semi-automatic blood farm for your blood altar, just so you can get enough LP. Villagers in a spawner from Draconic Evolution would do just fine I think. You get the villager's soul by using the reaper enchantment or by crafting it with a custom crafting recipe.
This is one of the 2 key items needed to make demon-shards or whatever they are called.
This is the second key item to get Demon Crystals things. This is the thing that actually makes them.

You may be thinking that these might be hard to get since they sound hard to get, but they really aren't.


All you need to do, is place down your demon crucible and crystalizer in the same chunk, then, with a full tartaric gem, I think it has to be atleast common, but I could be wrong, place it into the demon crucible by right clicking on it with it.

And done, now Demon will Crystals will spawn on top of the demon crystalizer and they can grow to hold 4 crystals max.

You can expand/make this setup faster by just adding more demon crystalizers to the setup.


Crystals will spawn when the Demon-Will is above 90 which can seen by using the reward from this quest, just shift to use it.
Have fun.

This is the final step before making terrasteel.

Make a checkerboard pattern using 5 living rock and 4 lapis blocks so that there is a living rock in the center. Place this thing in the middle on top of the living rock in the center.

To make terrasteel, you need atleast half of a mana pool to be full and then connect the mana pool to the thingy by using sparks.

After that, throw 1 mana steel, 1 mana diamond and 1 mana pearl on the thingy and right click the thingy. 

Sit back and watch the animation generate your terrasteel.

This are very useful since they actually draw the lines of mana transfer. Shift Right Click to place one on top of both the mana pool and the thingy plate and then bind them as you would mana spreaders but the mana pool one goes to the thingy one.
I'd highly reccomend you make the resource seed version of this since you will need a lot of it.
Make these items and I will guide you through the assembly of the elven portal gateway thingy in the next quest

SO. Here's-a how it goes-a. First place down your gateway core and the on the left and right of it place a living wood. You should now have a 3 block line of blocks. on each side of the living wood, go up one block and across then place your next living wood.

Ontop of the new living woods that you just placed, place a glimmering living wood followed by another living wood ontop of that.

Then just finish the pattern on top creating a portal with a 3x3 space inside of it.

NOW, on each side of the portal's frame, I'd say one (1;a;single;an) block away from infront of it, place your mana pools on the ground with the pylons right on top of them. 

Now fill your mana pools to about a quartar (either via sparks or generating mana there). Once you have done this, right click the elven core with your wand and BOOM. You now have the elven portal that you can't go through.

For more building instructions, read book or look at wiki.
